Upstream attribution
--------------------
Project Starfish salvages select non-security-critical components, under the
"strangler" build strategy, from the upstream project "munder-difflin"
(https://github.com/chaitanyagiri/munder-difflin), which is distributed under
the MIT License. The upstream MIT copyright and permission notice are retained
for those salvaged components. Every salvaged file and its origin are recorded
in docs/SALVAGE_LEDGER.md.

NOTE: The upstream project bundles pixel-art assets under a NON-COMMERCIAL
license (LimeZu FREE VERSION). Those assets are NOT used by Project Starfish.
All Project Starfish art is original (see docs/ART_PROVENANCE_LEDGER.md). A CI
scan (scripts/ip-denylist-scan.mjs) guards the shippable source against
third-party IP tokens.
